		"body": "Closes #12327 \r\n\r\n## Summary\r\nChecked checkboxes inside tables were shown as unchecked in the split-screen preview pane.\r\n\r\n## Root Cause\r\nThe preview pane never loaded Font Awesome. Checkboxes inside tables are stored as raw HTML with `<li class=\"checked\">` and rendered via CSS + FA icons (`ul.joplin-checklist li::before`). Without FA, the icon silently failed to render.\r\n\r\nRegular checklists outside tables are unaffected as they render as native `<input type=\"checkbox\">` elements.\r\n\r\n## Fix\r\nInject Font Awesome (already bundled in vendor dir) into the preview webview's `pluginAssets` array in `CodeMirror.tsx` (v5 & v6).\r\n\r\n## Testing\r\n1. Open Rich Text editor\r\n2. Insert a table and add a checked checklist item inside a cell\r\n3. Switch to split-screen (Markdown + preview)\r\n4. Verify checked checkbox renders correctly in preview\r\n\r\n## Demo\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/user-attachments/assets/ac5de7af-310d-4315-a525-2230ee353a7b\r\n\r\n",
